Amy-Leigh Hickman https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Amy-Leigh_Hickman 0 Amy-Leigh Hickman (born Amy Leigh Hickman; 16 September 1997) is an English actress best known for her childhood role as Carmen Howle in CBBC's Tracy Beaker Returns its sequel, The Dumping Ground. As an adult, Hickman is best known for her recurring role of Linzi Bragg in BBC soap opera EastEnders, Sia Marshall in the Netflix series Safe and Nasreen Paracha in Channel 4's school drama, Ackley Bridge.
